 3.  Terminology
 
-   This document will follow the terms defined in [RFC8724], [RFC8376],
-   and [TR23720].
+   This document follows the terms defined in [RFC8724], [RFC8376],
+   [TR23720], and [DRAFT-SCHC-ARCH].
+
+   SCHC Endpoint:  A logical entity that provides SCHC functionality by
+      hosting the SCHC processing code, as defined in [DRAFT-SCHC-ARCH].
+      Physical 3GPP nodes (Dev-UE, RGW-eNB, NGW-MME, Application Server)
+      host SCHC Endpoints.
+
+   SCHC Instance:  A logical component of an Endpoint that executes actual
+      SCHC operations (C/D and F/R) using a specific Context and Instance
+      Configuration, as defined in [DRAFT-SCHC-ARCH].
+
+   Session:  A communication session between two or more Instances that
+      share a common Context, as defined in [DRAFT-SCHC-ARCH].
+
+   Stratum:  The portion of the network protocol stack targeted by SCHC
+      (e.g., Application, PDCP, or NAS), defining the scope of protocol
+      headers addressed by Rules, as defined in [DRAFT-SCHC-ARCH].
+
+   Dispatcher:  A logical component of the Endpoint that routes incoming
+      packets to the appropriate Instance based on a Discriminator, as
+      defined in [DRAFT-SCHC-ARCH].
+
+   Discriminator:  Information element (e.g., 3GPP bearer ID, IP tunnel ID,
+      or API session metadata) used by the Dispatcher to route packets to
+      the appropriate Instance, as defined in [DRAFT-SCHC-ARCH].
+
+   Domain:  A logical grouping of Instances sharing a common set of
+      Contexts within the 3GPP network operator environment.
 
